title: 53Cr(n,ng) reactions and the level structure of 53Cr

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.39, p.1736 (1989)

x4freetext: Experiment performed at ORELA. Electron with
energy 140 MeV impinged on tantalum target produced
bremstrahlung, which subsequently produced
photoneutrons in tantalum target. Neutrons were
guided to the experimental area by an evacuated 20 m
long flight tube, located at 120 deg with respect to
the electron beam.
Sample was Cr2O3, encapsulated in cylindrical nylon
container of 2.9 cm diamater and 6.7cm height,
having a mass of 49g and isotopic enrichment of
95.4% in the 53Cr isotope
A large volume Ge(Li) detector was placed at
40 cm from the sample at a scattering angle of 125 deg.
Neutron energy uncertainty from time-of-flight
